Northern Irish Economic Strife Contributes to Terrorism, FT Says

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-02-24T01:46:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/northern-irish-economic-strife-contributes-to-terrorism-ft-says.html
Economic decline in Northern Ireland
may have caused a recent spike in terrorist activity there, the
Financial Times reported, citing unidentified people involved in  Northern Ireland  security.  There is an economic aspect to the recruitment of
dissidents in Northern Ireland, the newspaper cited a security
official as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in  London  at 
 jjordan22@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 